snippet.title: New Update - Town Hall 16 in Clash of Clans!
snippet.description:
TH16 Update Sneak Peek for Clash of Clans! Judo Sloth Gaming shares Town Hall 16 Gameplay as well as information on New Troop and Defense Levels coming in the update. There are numerous building upgrades shared alongside Balance Changes, Cost Reductions and the ability to finally attack your own base! This is only Sneak Peek 1 for the CoC December Update so be sure to subscribe for more Town Hall 16 content. The exact TH16 release date is not confirmed yet but it is typically shortly after sneak peeks and will be after Hammer Jam is finished. Clash On!

snippet.title: New Hero and Troop Abilities Explained (Clash of Clans)
snippet.description:
The Battle Copter is the New Hero in Builder Base 2.0 Update! Clash of Clans Sneak Peeks begin for the CoC Update and in this video Judo Sloth Gaming provides a guide for every troop ability as well as the Hero Reworks. The Battle Copter is the New Hero at BH8 but the Battle Machine is also redesigned as now there are charge levels. The Multi-Stage Builder Base 2.0 update means you can switch heroes between the two stages and New Buildings including OTTOs Outpost, the Healing Hut and Reinforcement Camp are also explained. Subscribe for all the update sneak peeks!

snippet.title: New Loot and Trophy System Explained for Builder Base 2.0!
snippet.description:
There is No Loot Limit in the Clash of Clans Builder Base 2.0 Update! Sneak Peek 2 reveals a New Trophy System with Leagues for Builder Base. Judo Sloth Gaming explains everything you need to know as climbing the Leagues in Builder Base will help you with more loot and provide a greater Star Bonus. The mechanisms act similar to Legend League from the Home Village but with a few differences; mainly that you gain Builder Gold from Attacking and Builder Elixir from Defending! Be sure to subscribe for more CoC update sneak peeks and check out yesterdays video explaining the New Battle Copter Hero and Troop Abilities. Clash On!

snippet.title: New Recall Spell and Battle Drill Explained (Clash of Clans)
snippet.description:
The New Town Hall 15 Update brings a New Spell and New Siege Machine to Clash of Clans! Judo Sloth Gaming shares the Recall Spell and Battle Drill gameplay in this tutorial guide style sneak peek. I wanted to assure you fully knew how the new spell worked alongside attack strategy for its best use. The Recall Spell is incredibly unique and probably the most fun spell we have ever seen in CoC. It's strategy is in being able to take advantage of weaknesses in a base design, as you will see in the video. The Battle Drill is a New Siege Machine which is defense targeting and can stun them too. I think the Battle Drill is the Best Siege Machine to date. The TH15 Update is huge, this is only sneak peek 4, they are still going, so be sure to subscribe as I will be explaining all of the new content to you. Clash On!

snippet.title: World Record for TH2 in Masters League!
snippet.description:
The World Record for Town Hall 2 in Clash of Clans. Judo Sloth Gaming shares the story of a TH2 Player who hit Master League whilst Trophy Pushing. The Attack Strategy of choice was Barch but there was a lot of information shared including Base Design and Shield Management. Whilst 5 years ago there was a TH2 Titan Player, the game mechanics changed and this is no longer possible, this is the New World Record after that change. Ever since the TH6 Legend video I have been interested in exactly how low TH level player push high in trophies so I wanted to share this next story with you. Thank you to Spuon for sharing your story. Good luck to all of the low level trophy pushers. Clash On!

localized.title: World Record for TH2 in Masters League!
localized.description:
The World Record for Town Hall 2 in Clash of Clans. Judo Sloth Gaming shares the story of a TH2 Player who hit Master League whilst Trophy Pushing. The Attack Strategy of choice was Barch but there was a lot of information shared including Base Design and Shield Management. Whilst 5 years ago there was a TH2 Titan Player, the game mechanics changed and this is no longer possible, this is the New World Record after that change. Ever since the TH6 Legend video I have been interested in exactly how low TH level player push high in trophies so I wanted to share this next story with you. Thank you to Spuon for sharing your story. Good luck to all of the low level trophy pushers. Clash On!

snippet.title: Never Miss the 2 Star! Electro Dragon Attacks in Legend League (Clash of Clans)
snippet.description:
The Electro Dragon TH13 Attack Strategy brings a comfortable and flexible 2 Star Strategy with the opportunity for a 3 Star in Clash of Clans. This makes it perfect for the Clan War Leagues due to its ability to never miss the 2 stars. This is all due to the flexibility that the Electro Dragons offer The important parts are highlighted throughout my Legend Attacks but try and set up the funnel for them to access the Town Hall, take down Air Defence/Single Infernos first and Freeze the Sweepers! Always take note of your Plan B for a centralised TH, whether it be the Blimp, Royal Champ, or changing your E Drag entry mid attack. Let me know what you would like to see next in Legend League. Enjoy!

snippet.title: Starting the Builder Base - Let's Play the New CoC Update + YOUTUBER TOURNAMENT | Clash of Clans
snippet.description:
Beginning the Builder Base in this Lets Play Ep. 1 for Clash of Clans New Update. The Raged Barbarian is the first troop unlocked in the Builder Base and you may struggle initially to get going and win your first battles. Tips are provided in the video but main priorities are building the second army camp, protecting the defences, not the Builder Hall, and attacking! Remember guys, its free, it does not cost gold or elixir to attack so your best bet for the new update is to attack until you win your free loot in the daily bonus. No gems will be used on this lets play series as I want to provide tips and tricks for the new game mode as I progress and do so with most of my subscribers. snippet.title: How To Start Clash of Clans – Beginner Tips and Tutorial Guide
snippet.description:
A beginners guide for starting Clash of Clans. Tutorial gameplay provides tips and tricks on how to start CoC effectively. A new series of beginner gameplay and guides will be brought to you as we progress through the game. In this first lets play style episode we cover the very basics on buildings, troops and loot. I would recommend trying your best to upgrade Gold and Elixir mines, pumps and storages to improve loot production. Defences are important to keep a balanced base but you can utilise the free shield initially. Tips for saving gems are providing and I would advise spending gems on new builders to increase your upgrade rate. The first two troops from the Barracks are unlocked and shown, the Barbarian and the Archer. The Barbarian is a tank style troop whilst the Archer benefits from increased range. I hope this how to start Clash of Clans guide has been helpful and if you have any further tips for beginners please share them in the comment section below. Clash On!

snippet.title: Clash of Clans | How To Take Out The Enemy Clan Castle Troops - Beginners Guide
snippet.description:
Clash of Clans Guide! How to take out and kill enemy clan castle troops. This Clash of Clans beginner guide provides tips to easily take out the enemy clan castle troops. Just remember to 'Kill It and Fill It'. If you're new to Clash of Clans this is a fundamental skill that you will have to learn in order to have success within the game. To maximise your chances of the 3 star attack in war, always fill your own clan castle. Your clan can donate you strong or even max level troops which will massively help at low level; I would recommend Hog Riders or Balloons. The first and most important thing you then have to do when you start the attack is to take out the defending clan castle troops; Fill it and Kill it! There are a number of ways to do this but all of the basics are covered in the video. In summary: you need to put one of your troops inside the 'trigger radius' of the enemy clan castle. This will 'lure out' the defending troops; I would recommend using a Giant to do this when you are starting out. You then need to draw the troops to an area of the map where you are out of range of defences and can therefore just concentrate on the castle troops. Make sure to surround the enemy troops so that they cannot do splash damage on your troops. The easiest strategy that I would recommend for beginners is to circle the enemy clan castle troops with Archers. A few more advanced and efficient methods are touched upon in the video but for the most part this video is targeted towards beginners. If you have become used to killing the enemy clan castle with 2 Poison Spells - double poison method, then you might want to revisit how to take out the enemy clan castle troops as balance changes are coming to Clash of Clans in the next update and you will no longer be able to use this method. Read all about the new balance changes announced by Supercell in the article below. If you have any other tips for taking out the defending clan castle troops, please share them in the comments below. Enjoy!

Clash of Clans Balance Changes: https://supr.cl/BalanceChanges_March16

snippet.title: Official Call of Duty®: WWII – ‘Brotherhood of Heroes’ Documentary
snippet.description:
Call of Duty®: WWII will take players to the front lines of war-torn Western Europe during one of history’s greatest conflicts, where the stakes were high and the only thing standing in the way of Nazi oppression was a generation of ordinary men and women willing to make extraordinary sacrifices to preserve our way of life.

Get a peek at how Sledgehammer Games pays homage to the men and women who answered history’s call through a gripping Campaign Mode that aims to redefine World War II for a new generation of gamers. The journey begins on November 3.

Get the full Call of Duty®: WWII Campaign mission briefing: https://www.callofduty.com/wwii/campaign

snippet.title: Official Call of Duty® XP 2016 Announce Trailer
snippet.description:
The ultimate 3-day Call of Duty fan celebration is back! This September 2-4 in Los Angeles, Call of Duty® XP 2016 will deliver an unforgettable weekend of incredible events for thousands of Call of Duty fans, culminating in the 2016 Call of Duty World League Championship.
 
Be among the first in the world to get hands-on with Call of Duty®: Infinite Warfare Multiplayer, Call of Duty®: Modern Warfare Remastered Multiplayer, Call of Duty®: Infinite Warfare Zombies, and Call of Duty®: Black Ops 3 DLC 4 before anyone else! Jump into the action with real-life Nuketown paintball, zombies laser tag, an exclusive PlayStation VR experience, and other Call of Duty-inspired activities throughout the weekend, and cheer on your favorite Call of Duty® World League teams throughout the Call of Duty® Championship, all weekend long. This is an event that fans will be talking about for years to come. 
 
Have questions about COD XP 2016? Read the FAQ here: http://www.callofduty.com/xp
Pre-order the Legacy Edition or Digital Deluxe Edition and get Call of Duty®: Modern Warfare® Remastered*, the return of one of the most critically-acclaimed games of all time.
 
*Call of Duty®: Modern Warfare® Remastered contains only 10 MP maps from the original Call of Duty®: Modern Warfare® game. For more information, please visit www.callofduty.com/MWR_FAQ

localized.title: Official Call of Duty® XP 2016 Announce Trailer
localized.description:
The ultimate 3-day Call of Duty fan celebration is back! This September 2-4 in Los Angeles, Call of Duty® XP 2016 will deliver an unforgettable weekend of incredible events for thousands of Call of Duty fans, culminating in the 2016 Call of Duty World League Championship.
 
Be among the first in the world to get hands-on with Call of Duty®: Infinite Warfare Multiplayer, Call of Duty®: Modern Warfare Remastered Multiplayer, Call of Duty®: Infinite Warfare Zombies, and Call of Duty®: Black Ops 3 DLC 4 before anyone else! Jump into the action with real-life Nuketown paintball, zombies laser tag, an exclusive PlayStation VR experience, and other Call of Duty-inspired activities throughout the weekend, and cheer on your favorite Call of Duty® World League teams throughout the Call of Duty® Championship, all weekend long. This is an event that fans will be talking about for years to come. 
 
Have questions about COD XP 2016? Read the FAQ here: http://www.callofduty.com/xp
Pre-order the Legacy Edition or Digital Deluxe Edition and get Call of Duty®: Modern Warfare® Remastered*, the return of one of the most critically-acclaimed games of all time.

snippet.title: Official Call of Duty®: Infinite Warfare – Absolution Trailer
snippet.description:
Take the fight to all-new locations in Call of Duty®: Infinite Warfare’s latest DLC pack, Absolution. Play through a massive mini-golf park in Fore, the frozen inner city of Permafrost, an oceanic shanty town in Bermuda, and Call of Duty®: Modern Warfare 3's fan-favorite Resistance, now re-imagined as Ember. 

Infinite Warfare Zombies goes back in time to the 1950s with Attack of the Radioactive Thing! Lead by Elvira, the Mistress of the Dark herself, our ever-revolving cast of survivors must save a small '50s beach town from a government science experiment gone horribly wrong.

Get Infinite Warfare’s third DLC pack, Absolution, first on PS4 July 6th: http://bit.ly/COD-IW

snippet.title: Profile Highlights: Fariko Impact Lookback - Call of Duty® World League Presented by PlayStation 4
snippet.description:
In its inaugural year, Call of Duty Championship 2013 held fans and players by a thread in a heated Grand Final that pushed the limits to a Game 11, S&D Round 10 finish. As Fariko Impact, Karma, Killa, MiRx, and Parasite overcame Team EnVyUs to become the first Call of Duty esports world champions. Watch the looking back video to see how a world championship win changed these players and ignited their dreams to compete in the Call of Duty World League, presented by PlayStation 4.

Follow us for the latest in Call of Duty esports:

snippet.title: Profile Highlights: XP Pioneers - Call of Duty® World League Presented by PlayStation 4
snippet.description:
Call of Duty XP is fast approaching. Mr. X sits down with competitive Call of Duty veterans Clayster, Pacman, Swanny, and TeePee to discuss the progress of Call of Duty eSports over the years. The first XP took place in 2011, with 32 teams competing for $1 million in what was then the biggest Call of Duty tournament to date. Call of Duty Championships 2013, 2014 and 2015 followed suit, impressing the fact that the competitive Call of Duty scene was growing and players could solidify their place in esports history.

Follow us for the latest in Call of Duty esports:

Twitter: https://twitter.com/CODWorldLeague
